  "script": "Skateboarding across America? One guy just rode a skateboard from California all the way to Florida — roughly 3,000 miles — in 39 days, chasing his own Guinness World Record. Do the math: that's pushing a skateboard the length of a country, every single day, on highways, through heat, on a board the size of a cutting board. His feet did what most people's cars do on a road trip. By the end he'd worn through wheels, dodged traffic, and turned a kid's toy into an endurance machine. Most of us can't skate to the corner store without eating pavement. So could you push a skateboard 3,000 miles without quitting on day one?",
